RABIES VACCINATION, BOOSTERS
****************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Sun, 23 Aug 1998 16:42:31 -0300
From: Phyllis Catharina Romijn <phyllis@openlink.com.br>

Rabies among bats is increasing in the State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, not
only _D. rotundus_ but also non-haematophagous bats. As technicians and
researchers monitoring and controlling roosts, we get in close contact with
these mammals, and used to have our antibody levels checked every year,
with a booster when titer is lower as 0.5 IU. It has been discussed that
the Fuenzalida-Palacios vaccine, which we use normally, is less
immunogenic, and would protect less, than the human diploid cell vaccine.
The latter should also give better protection against other genotypes than
the genotype 01.
Is it possible to comment on the subject?
--
Phyllis Catharina Romijn,
researcher at PESAGRO-RIO,
Niteroi, Rio de Janeiro, Brasil
e-mail: phyllis@openlink.com.br
